translated: Millqvist, Johan Ragnar, Lieutenant Colonel, Sjötuna, Axvalil, b. 12/2/86 in Slöta, Skaraborg County, son of landowner August M. and Alma Boiström. Married 1st on 11/34 to Kerstin Erikson; 2nd on 35 to Eivor Sundberg. Children: Svante b. 12, Tord b. 13, Folke b. 15, Eva b. 17, Roilf b. 20, Sten b. 23, Ragnar b. 39. Military: Enlisted in Skara 04, resigned from active duty in 06, attended the Royal Military Academy 12-14. Served as Second Lieutenant in Älvsborg Regiment in 06, promoted to Lieutenant in 09, Captain in 21, Major in the Army in 30, transferred to Skaraborg Regiment in 32, promoted to Lieutenant Colonel in the reserve of Skaraborg Regiment in 40. Served as Assistant in the General Staff 16-18, Regimental Adjutant 19-21, Adjutant in the Military Inspectorate 22-26, Company Commander in the Military Intelligence 26-29, served in the General Staff 29-30, Military Attaché in Poden 30-33, Chief of Enlistment in 42-46. Served in the German Army in 26. Chairperson of the Falköping Shooting Association 40-43, Chairperson of the Swedish Genealogical Society Skaraborg District since 44, Commander of the Vara Home Guard District. Received the Royal Order of the Sword, Officer Diploma in Political Science, Shooting Medal.
